// ============================================================
// ME327 Team 10 - Force Model Tester (Processing)
// ============================================================
// Multi-shape version. Three shapes (bunny, hammer, pear) derived from
// the same Python-generated CSVs that feed the Arduino code.
//
// Two modes:
//   STANDALONE  : compute the force model in Processing itself
//                 (no Arduino needed -- fastest way to validate the math)
//   HARDWARE    : stream mouse position to an Arduino over serial,
//                 receive force back, render it
//
// Visual:
//   - Black outline = active shape
//   - Light blue band = dead zone (P_T < d < 0, F = 0)
//   - Light red band = guidance region (d < P_T, exponential pull)
//   - Pink dot = mouse / pen-tip position
//   - Green arrow = force vector on the user
//   - Top-left HUD: shape, mode, depth, force
//
// Controls:
//   B / H / P keys : switch to Bunny / Hammer / Pear
//   T key          : toggle MODE_CONTROL <-> MODE_TEXTURED
//   M key          : toggle STANDALONE <-> HARDWARE
//   R key          : reset velocity state
// ============================================================

import processing.serial.*;

// ---------- MODE SELECTION ----------
